<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-30T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-30T18:00:00-05:00" n="1449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1449">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.953/9–3049: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hawthorne</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-30T18:00:00-05:00">September
                                    30, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>298. Dept considers it necessary for you close office immed and depart
                            soonest reDeptel 271, Sep 14.<note n="13" xml:id="d1449fn13">Not
                                printed.</note> Inform Dept soonest when and how you and staff
                            expect depart. Sep[arate] tel fols personnel assignments. Inform Dept
                            whether difficulties encountered in obtaining exit permits or if any
                            Dept action necessary assist departure.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>